## 2. Frontend Implementation Status
> [!WARNING]
> A React + Tailwind frontend structure has **NOT** been detected in the project yet. Currently, there are only basic Django HTML templates ([login.html](file:///c:/Users/Jhenkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Jhenkar/Project/wanderlust/users/templates/login.html), [dashboard.html](file:///c:/Users/Jhenkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Jhenkar/Project/wanderlust/users/templates/dashboard.html), [listings.html](file:///c:/Users/Jhenkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Jhenkar/Project/wanderlust/users/templates/listings.html), [my_listings.html](file:///c:/Users/Jhenkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Jhenkar/Project/wanderlust/users/templates/my_listings.html)) serving as placeholders.
- **Pages created:** None (in React).
- **Components:** None (in React).
- **Axios Integration:** None.
- **UI Sections:** None.

---

## 3. Features Currently Working (Backend API)
- ✅ **Dynamic API fetching & JSON outputs**: The DRF setup properly outputs JSON for authentication and listings.
- ✅ **Featured Listings**: The `/api/listings/featured/` endpoint functional with sorting by rating (`-rating`).
- ✅ **Pagination**: Featured endpoint delivers paginated results (6 per page).
- ✅ **JWT Authentication Framework**: Access & refresh logic built into login functionality.
- ✅ **Role-Based Access Control**: Admins can approve Hosts. Only Approved Hosts can create listings.

---

## 4. Folder Structure Overview
**Backend (`wanderlust/`)**
- `/core/`: Core Django settings ([settings.py](file:///c:/Users/Jhenkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Jhenkar/Project/wanderlust/core/settings.py), core [urls.py](file:///c:/Users/Jhenkar/OneDrive/Desktop/Jhenkar/Project/wanderlust/core/urls.py))
- `/users/`: Custom user handling, JWT serializers, Auth models, and Django HTML templates.
- `/listings/`: Models, serializers, & views dedicated to properties.
- `manage.py`, `requirement.txt`, `db.sqlite3`

**Frontend**
- *Currently missing.*

---

## 5. Database State
- **Database Engine**: SQLite (`db.sqlite3` is present in root).
- **Migrated Fields**: Both `User` and `Listing` schemas are actively present and likely migrated.
- **Relationships**: `Listing` correctly inherits a `ForeignKey` relationship to the `User` model, acting as the Host.

---

## 6. What Is NOT Yet Implemented

- **React Frontend Setup**: Create project using Vite or Next.js, implement Tailwind configuration, build components.
- **Search & Filters Functionality**: Missing search endpoint/queries by location, price, dates.
- **Booking / Reservation System**: No `Booking` model exists yet to lock dates/availability. 
- **Payments Integration**: No models/endpoints for Stripe/Razorpay.
- **Image Uploads**: `Listing.image` is a simple `URLField`. Cloudinary/AWS S3 for actual image upload functionality is not built.
- **Full Admin Controls**: Basic host approval exists, but comprehensive application management is lacking.

---

## 7. Overall Project Level
- **Current Status**: **Beginner/Intermediate (Backend-focused)** 
- **To make it Portfolio-Ready**: 
  1. Initialize the React/Tailwind frontend and connect it via Axios to the existing endpoints.
  2. Implement a complete Booking architecture (handling dates/overlapping checks).
  3. Replace `URLField` image endpoints with real Multipart FormData uploads (S3 or Cloudinary).
  4. Build dynamic Search & Filtering backend support using `django-filter` or custom querysets.

---

## 8. Clear Summary

**☑️ Completed Features**
- Custom User Model (Admin, Host, User Roles)
- JWT Authentication (Login, Register, Refresh)
- Admin controls to review and approve Host applications
- Listing creation bounded by Approved Host permissions
- Featured Listings fetching with Pagination and `select_related` DB optimization

**⏳ Pending Features**
- **The Entire React/Tailwind Frontend**
- Robust Search & Filtering capabilities
- Booking and Reservation data structures
- Image file uploading functionality
- Payment gateway integrations
